What Are AI Moderators and Virtual Hosts?

AI Moderators are intelligent systems that assist during live webinars by:

Managing Q&A sessions in real-time

Curating audience questions and comments

Offering helpful resources based on conversation topics

Analyzing attendee sentiment and engagement levels

Virtual Hosts, on the other hand, act as digital presenters or co-hosts. They:

Welcome attendees with personalized greetings

Guide participants through the agenda

Present pre-recorded or AI-generated content dynamically

Offer interactive polls, surveys, and chat prompts

Trigger smart call-to-actions based on behavior

These technologies make it possible to run webinars at scale â€” without sacrificing personalization or human-like interaction.

